summary: The purpose of this article is to compare the chemical composition and antimicrobial potency of essential oils obtained from different parts of Saudi Anethum graveolens L. using headspace solid-phase microextraction (HS-SPME) and gas chromatography-mass spectrometry (GC-MS).

use_cases.case: The genomic data represented by the provided accession is not accessed or used in this study. Rather, the accession is mentioned for the purpose of referring to a specific species of bacteria (Enterobacter hormaechei subsp. xiangfangensis) against which the authors assayed the antibacterial activity of certain essential oils.
